==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Diversity
<hw>Di*ver"si*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Diversities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>diversit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, L. <ets>diversitas</ets>, fr.
<ets>diversus</ets>. See <er>Diverse</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
state of difference; dissimilitude; unlikeness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They will prove opposite; and not resting in a bare
<qex>diversity</qex>, rise into a contrariety.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Multiplicity of difference; multiformity;
variety.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Diversity</xex> of sounds.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Shak.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Diversities</xex> of opinion.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Secker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Variegation.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Bright
<xex>diversities</xex> of day.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Variety</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diversivolent</ent>⟦br⟧
